<h2>Engagement and Query Volume</h2>
<p><strong>14. ChatGPT processes approximately 2.5 billion prompts per day.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/chatgpt-statistics/">DemandSage</a> / The Verge, 2026
That is roughly 29,000 prompts per second, every second of every day.</p>
<p><strong>15. Users send approximately 18 billion messages per week.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://openai.com/index/how-people-are-using-chatgpt/">OpenAI</a>, 2025
OpenAI published this figure in their NBER research paper on ChatGPT usage patterns.</p>
<p><strong>16. Average session duration is 6 minutes and 5 seconds.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.similarweb.com/website/chatgpt.com/">Similarweb</a>, 2026
That is significantly longer than the average Google search session of 1-2 minutes.</p>
<p><strong>17. Users view an average of 3.73 pages per visit.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.similarweb.com/website/chatgpt.com/">Similarweb</a>, 2026
Multi-page sessions suggest users engage in extended conversations rather than one-off queries.</p>
<p><strong>18. Bounce rate sits at 31.83%.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.similarweb.com/website/chatgpt.com/">Similarweb</a>, 2026
A <a href="/glossary/bounce-rate/">bounce rate</a> under 40% indicates strong engagement for a web application.</p>
<p><strong>19. Approximately 30% of consumer ChatGPT usage is work-related. The remaining 70% is personal.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://openai.com/index/how-people-are-using-chatgpt/">OpenAI NBER Study</a>, 2025
Personal use includes learning, creative writing, and day-to-day problem solving.</p>
