<p><strong>21. ChatGPT generated approximately $8 billion for OpenAI in 2025, roughly 66% of total company revenue.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.businessofapps.com/data/chatgpt-statistics/">BusinessOfApps</a>, 2025
The remainder comes from API access, enterprise contracts, and partnerships.</p>
<p><strong>22. In-app purchase revenue hit $227 million in February 2026 alone.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/chatgpt-statistics/">DemandSage</a> / Statista, 2026
That is mobile revenue only. Desktop subscriptions are separate.</p>
<p><strong>23. ChatGPT Plus subscriptions account for 55% of OpenAI revenue.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.businessofapps.com/data/chatgpt-statistics/">BusinessOfApps</a>, 2025
The $20/month Plus plan remains the primary monetization vehicle.</p>
<p><strong>24. OpenAI has 50 million paid subscribers across Plus, Team, and Enterprise plans.</strong>
Source: <a href="https://www.businessofapps.com/data/chatgpt-statistics/">BusinessOfApps</a>, 2025
That gives ChatGPT a higher paid subscriber count than most SaaS companies in the world.</p>
