<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>How many people use ChatGPT in 2026?</strong></p>
<p>ChatGPT has 900 million weekly active users and approximately 210 million daily active users as of early 2026. Monthly visits to chatgpt.com exceed 5 billion.</p>
<p><strong>How much traffic does ChatGPT get per month?</strong></p>
<p>ChatGPT receives between 5.3 and 6.1 billion monthly visits depending on the month. January 2026 recorded 5.7 billion. October 2025 peaked at 6.1 billion.</p>
<p><strong>Is ChatGPT bigger than Google?</strong></p>
<p>No. Google receives 83.9 billion visits per month, roughly 14 times more than ChatGPT. However, ChatGPT processes approximately 12% of Google search volume, and that gap is closing. For more context, see our <a href="/blog/google-search-statistics/">Google search statistics</a> roundup.</p>
<p><strong>How much money does ChatGPT make?</strong></p>
<p>OpenAI reached $10 billion in annual recurring revenue as of mid-2025. ChatGPT generates approximately 66% of that, or about $8 billion annually. Plus subscriptions at $20/month are the largest revenue source.</p>
<p><strong>What percentage of Fortune 500 companies use ChatGPT?</strong></p>
<p>92% of Fortune 500 companies use ChatGPT. OpenAI has deployed 7 million enterprise seats across approximately 1.5 million business customers.</p>
<p><strong>Does ChatGPT send traffic to websites?</strong></p>
<p>Very little. ChatGPT accounts for only 0.21% of all website traffic, compared to Google at 40%. However, when ChatGPT does link out, users click at a rate of 1.4 links per visit versus 0.6 on Google. The traffic is concentrated on roughly 120 domains. Learn more in our guide on <a href="/blog/get-cited-ai-search/">how to get cited by AI search engines</a>.</p>
